<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
[[ Genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E0BC8DAD-9CD9-4E32-920A-063D33AD0E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hypostomus Lacépède 1803:144" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypostomus Lacépède</taxonomicName>
]]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E0BC8DAD-9CD9-4E32-920A-063D33AD0E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hypostomus Lacépède 1803:144" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypostomus</taxonomicName>
, the type genus of the subfamily Hypostominae, constitutes an assemblage of bottom-dwelling loricariid fishes widely distributed throughout South America, occurring in a variety of freshwater ecosystems such as small mountain streams and large lowland river areas. Maximum diversity in number of species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E0BC8DAD-9CD9-4E32-920A-063D33AD0E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hypostomus Lacépède 1803:144" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypostomus</taxonomicName>
occurs in rivers of the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paraná-Paraguay">Parana-Paraguay</normalizedToken>
system (Weber, 2003). As presently defined the genus consists of more than 130 nominal species (107 species considered valid by Weber, 2003 and expanded by Armbruster, 2004).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
Species level taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E0BC8DAD-9CD9-4E32-920A-063D33AD0E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hypostomus Lacépède 1803:144" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypostomus</taxonomicName>
is still poorly known as well as the phylogenetic relationships within and of the genus. 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E0BC8DAD-9CD9-4E32-920A-063D33AD0E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hypostomus Lacépède 1803:144" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypostomus</taxonomicName>
was established by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lacépède">Lacepede</normalizedToken>
(1803), who included in the genus only a single species, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:0FD754B5-0B7C-4E48-AA02-A19021C2013C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hypostomus guacari Lacépède 1803:144, 145" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guacari">H. guacari</taxonomicName>
. Old descriptions, similar to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lacépède">Lacepede</normalizedToken>
’s, and available for various subsequent species added to the genus, are very often scanty, with incomplete or poor characterization of species. This fact, together with a number of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E0BC8DAD-9CD9-4E32-920A-063D33AD0E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hypostomus Lacépède 1803:144" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypostomus</taxonomicName>
species yet to be described, makes the recognition of most taxa of the genus difficult. Hypothesis of phylogenetic relationships of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E0BC8DAD-9CD9-4E32-920A-063D33AD0E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hypostomus Lacépède 1803:144" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypostomus</taxonomicName>
based on molecular data (Montoya-Burgos et al., 1997, 2002) revealed that the genus does not form a natural group. According to these authors, some species currently assigned to 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E0BC8DAD-9CD9-4E32-920A-063D33AD0E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hypostomus Lacépède 1803:144" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypostomus</taxonomicName>
should be removed from the genus, while the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D72E8E8E-5BE4-4D83-85D5-1721B7808DA1" authority="Heckel, 1854" authorityName="Heckel" authorityYear="1854" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Cochliodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cochliodon Heckel 1854:255, 265" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cochliodon</taxonomicName>
should be treated as synonym of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E0BC8DAD-9CD9-4E32-920A-063D33AD0E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hypostomus Lacépède 1803:144" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypostomus</taxonomicName>
, an action effectuated by Weber &amp; Montoya-Burgos (2002: 265). Morphological based phylogenetic studies presented by Armbruster (2004) reinforce the conclusions above and place 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:253EC2D1-1550-4EC3-9C0A-D6486659393E" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Aphanotorulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Aphanotorulus Isbrücker &amp; Nijssen 1983:105" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Aphanotorulus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:0BB87056-F319-498D-9050-A6679F9A46B0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Isorineloricaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isorineloricaria Isbrücker 1980:15, 181" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isorineloricaria</taxonomicName>
in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E0BC8DAD-9CD9-4E32-920A-063D33AD0E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hypostomus Lacépède 1803:144" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypostomus</taxonomicName>
. In spite of the cited studies, more detailed phylogenetic analysis of the relationships within 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E0BC8DAD-9CD9-4E32-920A-063D33AD0E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hypostomus Lacépède 1803:144" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypostomus</taxonomicName>
awaits for future studies.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
The elevated number of species currently included in 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E0BC8DAD-9CD9-4E32-920A-063D33AD0E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hypostomus Lacépède 1803:144" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypostomus</taxonomicName>
, allied to the broad variability in morphology and color pattern of those taxa, poses difficulties for its entire revision. Various authors acquainted with these problems provided regional revisions of the genus, as exemplified by Boeseman (1968) with a study of the Surinam representatives of the genus, Weber (1985, 1986, 1987) that deals with 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E0BC8DAD-9CD9-4E32-920A-063D33AD0E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hypostomus Lacépède 1803:144" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypostomus</taxonomicName>
from Paraguay, more recently Reis et al. (1990) reviews and describes three new species from Southern Brazil, Mazzoni et al. (1994) provides a taxonomical revision of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E0BC8DAD-9CD9-4E32-920A-063D33AD0E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hypostomus Lacépède 1803:144" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypostomus</taxonomicName>
from Lower rio 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paraíba">Paraiba</normalizedToken>
do Sul, State of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, and finally Hollanda Carvalho &amp; Weber (2004) provided a revision of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7520B3CD-59C7-4425-A30E-1336A0B2AADD" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hypostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hypostomus cochliodon Kner 1854:265 [15]" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cochliodon">Hypostomus cochliodon group</taxonomicName>
from middle and lower Amazon system.
</paragraph>
